description.5: Gwen Stacy realizes moving to England might've been a major mistake. Meanwhile, Peter beats up Harry's drug dealer.
description.6: The dynamic duo is brought to an halt when Steve Rogers hangs up his winged cowl for the uniform of a police officer, the Falcon is left to fight alone!
description.7: Who is the mysterious Mr. Kline? Our horn-headed hero is dead set to find out, but first he's got to get past the rampaging Man-Bull! Offbeat, and totally awesome!
description.8: Bruce Banner is the Hulk no more! But what could make him risk his very life to become once again the green-skinned man-monster? Nothing except...Doc Samson!
description.9: Tony Stark and Iron Man are indeed one and the same, but when Tony finds himself going up against the wrath of the White Dragon, he must be in two places at once. Will Tony be able to keep up this charade? Or will his biggest secret be revealed?
description.11: Will Lady Sif appeal to Hela's feminine side to save Thor? Back on Asgard, Loki has stolen Odin's ring making him rightful ruler! Can Thor stop Loki before he attacks his first target- Earth?
description.12: Hulk vs. Thing by John Buscema? 'Nuff said.
description.14: The uncanny Inhumans face a hostile humanity - while it looks as if Black Bolt's out to destroy a whole city!
description.15: A robot on the loose and a man has his mind switched with an alien!
description.17: The last rites of Dorma! A soul-wrenching decision for a tormented Namor! Plus -- the untold truth about the Sub-Mariner's origin!
description.19: Norman Osborn's Green Goblin persona, once thought forgotten by Peter Parker, has returned. Now, Spider-Man must battle his greatest enemy over the skies of Manhattan.
description.20: Cap and Falcon face off against...Spider-Man?!
description.23: Ka-Zar runs into yet ANOTHER angry god! Dr. Doom has his eyes set on Wakanda, home of the Black Panther!
description.24: Two galvanizing guest-stars for the price of one! The Amazing Spider-Man and a fighting-mad Sub-Mariner! Plus, the weird threat that may destroy them all!
description.25: The Hulk has been teleported away to the far-off island of the Psyclops. The Psyclops are an ancient insectoid race that has been living off the radar. Will the Avengers be able to save the Hulk from his own rage against the aliens?
description.26: Iron Man finds himself in the middle of a gang war, when his good friend and coworker Frankie Majors is forced to return to the life of crime when Louise is kidnapped and held captive from the leader of the Gardenia gang.
description.28: Whoever expected anything like this to happen? The mighty Thor on the lam! But not even the Thunder God can run forever, and at the end he's caught...by Death!
description.29: The rampaging Thing turns the city of New York into a blazing battleground, as he attacks the Torch and Mr. Fantastic. And then- enter Bruce Banner!
description.31: What can we say about this one except -- Death strikes once more! Prince Namor's sunken world will never be the same again! And neither will you!
description.37: The Hulk has finally been subdued thanks to the help of Reed Richards and Charles Xavier. But just as Mr. Fantastic gets Hulk in a glass tube, the green brute is teleported away!
description.38: Wanting to prove himself worthy of being Captain America's partner, Falcon pursues the perceived menace of Spider-Ma
description.39: Fly high, DD, or die! The cataclysmic climax of Hornhead's epic clash with the mysterious El Condor, jam-packed with enough action to keep you glued to the edge of your seat!
description.40: Marvel's Not-So-Jolly Giant vs. Just About Everybody! The Leader. Sandman. The Abomination. The sensational Sub-Mariner...and a host of others! What has brought all of Hulk's foes out of the woodwork? With a final page worth waiting for.
description.41: Kevin, Pepper, and Happy race against the clock to save Tony's life. But things become riskier when Tony's failing suite might be the only thing to keep him alive. Or kill him instantly!
description.43: You've waited long enough. The startling, staggering, mind-boggling secret of Infinity! Another legend is born.
description.44: It had to happen. The FF couldn't go on forever. If you read no other comic this month, you must not miss "One From Four Leaves Three!" Featuring plenty of witchcraft!
description.45: Could this be the end of the line for King Black Bolt, leader of the Inhumans?
description.46: The wedding you thought would never happen! Namor marries the lady Dorma -- or does he? You'll gasp in amazement when you read the final panel!
description.48: A nation trembles in the ominous shadow of...El Condor! A story torn from today's front page, and dedicated to you, the Marvel breed of reader!
description.49: Once more, the Hulk takes on the super-powered Sandman- and this time it's for keeps! Plus, the shocking fate of Betty Ross! What health crisis is threatening her life?
description.50: Following his battle with the Zodiac and Spy-Master, Tony Stark finds himself going up against the superior Iron Man. Iron Man overworks himself causing strain on his heart that takes him out of the battle and to the brink of death.
description.52: Thor versus Odin...and the world's about to end! The coming of Karnilla and the evil Loki- and, above all, the triumph of Infinity!
description.53: Annihilus, the most deadly killer of all, waits in the Negative Zone! And our heroes must battle him, as we present...another Marvel death!
description.57: Dr. Doom and Ka-Zar both must face off against incredibly threatening enemies: Red Skull and Sun-God!
description.59: Peter Parker is on an official Daily Bugle assignment in London-a perfect opportunity to see out Gwen. However, when terrorists begin to stir up trouble, Peter must become Spider-Man to stop them.
description.60: It's the T-Challa/Black Panther origin story! During a quiet evening at the Mansion, the Avengers team convinces their teammate to open up about his mysterious past. It's the history of Wakanda and the untold legend of the Black Panther!
description.61: When Cap and a giant gorilla, are trapped in the underground lair of the Mole Man, it's up to the Falcon to rescue him!
description.64: An experimental device may destroy the Earth and the Avengers may accidentally lead to its detonation when they attack a group of Namor, Silver Surfer and the Hulk who are attempting to diffuse the device.
description.66: Black Bolt must prevent his brother Maximus from utilizing his new, disorienting powers!
description.68: The entire city is struck blind! Daredevil must uncover the reason for everyone's sudden loss of sight! Who is behind this massive epidemic?
description.69: The conclusion to the most far-out Hulk saga of all! And...the long-awaited fight-to-the-finish between Hulk and the awesome Abomination!
description.70: Iron Man, Daredevil, and Nick Fury team up to stop the Zodiac from possessing the Zodiac Key. But things take a turn for the worse when one of the good guys can't control its temptation! Who will fall to the Zodiac's power?
description.72: Even the title, "Worlds at War," can't begin to describe the excitement and wonder of this one! What happens to Thor is unbelievable- but Odin's fate? Wow.
description.73: His name is Janus, and he is the key to the most terrifying menace ever to face the Fantastic Four...and the whole human race.
description.75: An artist is given magic paint which brings his art to life!
description.76: Spider-Man attempts to rescue Aunt May after she is kidnaped by the Beatle!
description.77: After the Squadron Supreme releases their "Brain-Child One" rocket into space, the Avengers must save the day. Former Squadron member Nightwing provides assistance.
description.78: Get ready for Captain America and the Falcon to fight their most epic battle yet? Against a gorilla? Don't miss Captain America and Falcon as they take on a new kind of criminal!
description.80: In the clutches of the Zodiac Cartel, Daredevil, Iron Man, Madame Masque and Nick Fury find themselves at odds with formidable foes! Capricorn, Spymaster, Aquarius, and Sagittarius attack in an alien realm!
description.81: From beyond time and space comes the behemoth Klaatu- and the one they call Xeron the Star-Slayer! Who are these creatures dispatched to destroy the Hulk?
description.82: The fight against Spy-Master continues, as Tony Stark struggles to stay alive. Will Stark be able to overcome the master spy before he takes his last breath?
description.84: At last! A clue to the mysterious, monstrous entity known only as...Infinity! Plus, your very first glimpse into the weird and wondrous World Beyond.
description.85: Once again the dreaded Negative Zone threatens to destroy the entire world! But, just when he's needed most...what's happening to the Thing?
description.86: The Prowler is back! But the return of this villain is the least of Peter's worries because Gwen Stacy is leaving for England to stay with her uncle...for good.
description.87: The First Appearance of the Squadron Supreme!  Thor has had quite enough of Arkon and his tricks, and wields the power of Mjolnir to defeat him once and for all. Meanwhile, the Scarlet Witch reacquaints herself with her hex powers.
description.88: Captain America gets a new partner and co-star! Don't miss out on Cap's most exciting adventures yet!
description.91: Namor attempts to manipulate the Hulk and Silver Surfer into helping his cause, but when a dictator turns dangerous, all three will need to team-up to stop him.
description.92: Innocent townspeople need Ka-Zar's help! Meanwhile Dr. Doom goes on vacation not knowing the horrors he will see when he returns home…
description.99: Prince Namor's beloved subjects of Atlantis turn on him in a shocking issue...
